##Dictation | residential orders, party members and cadres "run errands" to buy food

The papernews

The function introduction, has the connotation the current politics new media

Speaker, He Zhiyong, member of the Standing Committee of the Yushui District Xinyu District Committee and head of the Publicity Department

Arrangement: Hu Guanghua, Zhang Qingqing

After much deliberation, Byron Mann and I, Chen Shan, decided to resist the pressure, starting from 9 pm on February 3, the Green Landscape waterfront community to implement full-closed management. The 13 health care workers who came into contact with the green scene waterfront community in Chunlong, a neighborhood in Xinyu where a suspected "super-spreader" named Huang lives, were infected.

New Crown Pneumonia (NCP) is a new type of infectious disease that has not been written in textbooks and has never been seen in reality. At first, people did not have enough understanding of its toxicity, infectivity and danger, and they were a little confused and did not take it seriously, it also coincides with the traditional Chinese festival, as if it was Spring Festival, people want to go to relatives go on a visit to relatives, want to go on a visit, did not take it seriously.

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Volunteer Service Point in a community in Yushui District, Xinyu, Jiangxi Province. Chinanews.com

In accordance with the unified deployment requirements of the municipal government of Xinyu, Jiangxi Province, on the evening of January 31, the Yushui District District Committee held a special meeting of four teams on the joint prevention and control of the epidemic of new pneumonia, in view of the current grim situation decided to semi-isolated management of all residential areas, and made a division of responsibility for the four groups of district leaders, each district leader to package a community.

I led the prevention and control of the epidemic in 13 districts of Chunlong community.

On the evening of February 2, we led the whole city in setting up the first temporary party branch in the community, with me as the Interim Party branch secretary, returning Party member, Liu Wenfeng, director of the Inspection Office of the Municipal Party Committee, Chen Shan, Director of the Talent Office of the Municipal Party Committee, Xiao Manzhu, Deputy Secretary of the Party Committee (Deputy Director) of the District Education and Sports Bureau, will serve as deputy secretary, district Party Committee Propaganda Department, District Bureau of Education and Sports Party member cadres and Chunlong community director, staff as members of the branch, the Temporary Party branch to the district prevention and control work general dispatch, General Coordination.

After the implementation of fully closed management, the temporary party branch re-scheduling, 24 hours in the area at the gate on guard. In order to ensure the supply of daily necessities for residents during the period of closure, starting from 3 February, the branch arranged for five party members, volunteers and returning teachers to work at 8:30 Every day, to The supermarket to help residents purchase fresh vegetables, fruits, rice, flour, oil and all kinds of daily necessities, to 20 downstairs, and then by the property staff door-to-door.

At the beginning of the implementation of full closed management, some residents do not understand, from time to time there are small contradictions, small disputes, small friction, and even Chong card, abuse. But considering that this is for the good of the community residents, for the good of the city, party members and volunteers have endured, willing to continue to be a good "gatekeeper, escort. ".

It is the first one in the whole city to carry out completely closed management

Early in the morning on February 1, I led the main responsible comrades of the District Party Committee Publicity Department, the District Education and Sports Bureau, the District Financial Media Center and the Chunlong community of Baopian help units to carry out a research and mapping on foot in 13 small districts, to understand the situation of epidemic prevention and control in each district.

At around 1:00 noon, we held a meeting in the community to analyze and compare the situation of epidemic prevention and control in Chunlong community, and made a specific division of labor among the 54 cadres of the three packing units, each cell command a section-level cadres as a group leader, clear their respective tasks and responsibilities.

There are more than 4500 residents living in more than 1300 households in lvjing waterfront residential area. After the semi-isolation was implemented in the community, from February 2 to 3, we have been closely watching and guarding at the gate of the community: Although semi-isolation has been implemented, the vehicles in and out are as busy as ever, and the people in and out are also like shopping in a supermarket, residents have all sorts of reasons to be in and out, and some don't take the epidemic seriously at all. It's not gonNA work like this.

After much deliberation, Byron Mann and Chen Shan and I decided to resist the pressure and start a completely closed management of the community from 9pm on February 3. Cars are only allowed to leave and not allowed to enter, and those that leave can only park outside, residents with epidemic prevention and control tasks and work needs must enter and exit with their unit certificates and identity cards, while other residents will arrange one person per household to go out every two days to purchase daily necessities according to the pass, in and out of the residential area residents must be registered for temperature testing.

Soon, the flow of traffic was greatly reduced. On the evening of February 6, several comrades of the Provisional Party branch discussed simply "one-size-fits-all" , banning all vehicles from entering and leaving. We believe that we can not go in the wrong direction. We are also responsible to the Party organizations at higher levels and to the people.

After the implementation of completely closed management, the Temporary Party branch rearranged shifts to ensure that 24-hour people are on guard at the gate of the district. Starting on the evening of February 3, I took the lead in maintaining the night shift from 8 pm to 12 pm. At the beginning of the closed administration, some residents did not understand. Party members and volunteers tried to explain and persuade them. Still, from time to time, there were minor conflicts, minor disputes, minor frictions, and even angry cards and invective. Some said, "other communities are not so strict, why do you care so much? " Some said, "I'm going to pull some vegetables out of the vegetable field and eat something fresh. " Some said, "I go for a walk in Beihu Park every day. It's an old habit. " ... But considering that it's for the good of the neighborhood and the city, the Party members and volunteers put up with it again and again, continue to act as gatekeeper and escort.

On the suspected "super communicator" residential building hidden trouble re-check

The 20 buildings in the LVJING waterfront community are occupied by a suspected "super communicator" in Xinyu, which has a total of 42 households and 163 people. In accordance with the deployment of the higher level, the building on January 29 implemented a fully closed management. February 2 afternoon, the city's main leaders came to the district unannounced visit, found that 20 residential areas isolated there are management loopholes, although the building access door locked, but residents can take the elevator from the underground garage access.

After learning this, the temporary party branch, together with the community director and the property manager, dealt with it immediately. Originally, they wanted to find a welder to seal the door of the underground garage, but it was the Spring Festival, and they also heard that it was the building where the "super communicator" lived, find a few masters are not willing to come, finally found often to help the district propaganda department repair he master, just sent a big lock, the underground garage channel completely locked.

At about 10:00 p.m. on February 3, the city received a public opinion express from the city's main leaders, saying that some netizens reported that 20 building 1702 residents were doing business in Hubei, and that a car with Hubei license plates was parked downstairs, posing a potential safety hazard in the epidemic.

After being informed of the situation, under the command of deputy mayor he of the municipal government, I led the comrades of the branch to quickly coordinate an investigation team composed of street, community cadres, property managers and public security police, on the morning of February 4,1702 owners of the basic situation carried out a home mapping.

According to the information provided by the traffic police department and the information obtained from home visits, the three members of the family in room 1702 all work in Xinyu and bought a car with Hubei license plates in 2019. They have been driving in Xinyu and have never been to Hubei, let alone Wuhan. Although several toss about, but we are hanging a heart finally put down.

In order to better manage the isolation of 42 households in 20 buildings, six volunteers have been on duty at the bottom of 20 buildings every five hours since February 4, prevent very few involuntary residents to take advantage of the property staff to transport supplies, collection of garbage from the building, to eliminate any potential spread of the virus.

After all closed management, residents of the car out of the community can not be parked outside, just a little random parking, crowded in the community gate, the surrounding sidewalk, even the community fire channel blocked.

Seeing this phenomenon, I called for the support of the head of the municipal traffic police detachment, Yuan Zhi. On the morning of February 4, the detachment arranged the traffic police to clean up the traffic at the entrance of the residential area. In spite of the rain, four guardrails were installed at the entrance of the residential area, to prevent the car parked randomly, to protect the community fire passageway, and from the 4th afternoon, the detachment sent two traffic police squatting at the gate of the Green Scene Waterfront community on guard.

After a week of strict control, we slowly steady foot, the traffic flow, the flow of people dropped significantly, whether residents to and from the body temperature monitoring registration, or parking cars outside, all become orderly.

For 20 building 42 households 163 people in complete isolation, the temporary party branch heart and soul to protect their daily life supplies. Starting from February 3, the branch arranged five volunteer party members and returning teachers to go to the supermarket every day at 8:30 to help them buy fresh vegetables, fruits, rice, noodles, oil and various daily necessities, and deliver them to the 20 buildings below, then by the property staff door to door.

This "vegetable basket" team of red vests carries 20 residents' orders printed from the Property Office to buy at least eighteen or five or six items each morning, each household is packed in separate bags, each household pays the bill with money, keeps a check against the order form over and over again to count the supplies, so as not to buy too little and forget to buy something, and spends two or three hours every day in the bustling supermarket, during this most taboo period of gathering, they are very brave, their dedication touched me, but also deeply touched the 20 building 42 residents.

In fact, the purchase of supplies is only a red vest "vegetable basket" team members volunteers work, they help residents purchase every day, but also participate in the community on duty, while taking care of their own work at hand. For example, comrade Zhang Qingqing of the press unit of the Publicity Department of the District Party Committee, immediately after the procurement, he had to rush to the unit to do a good job in the epidemic news publicity, Public Opinion Monitoring and disposal work; Yan Xiaoli, a member of the District Party Committee's Publicity Department, is also on night duty from 8 to 12 every night.

In addition to the material security of life, we are also very concerned about the isolation of the residents of psychological counseling. When I first moved into the community, I asked director he liuying of Chunlong community to pull me into the wechat exchange group of 20 residents. On the one hand, we will actively carry out exchanges in the community, relay the latest epidemic prevention and control measures of the municipal, municipal and district Party committees and district governments, and pass on some positive information, interact with them, and give everyone a boost of confidence. On the other hand, party members from the 163 residents of the 42 families in the 20 buildings were called on to reveal their identities in the form of a continuous line of fire. A total of 24 party members were found.

Since February 5, the 24 members of the Chinese Communist Party have played a good role as role models in the group. They have done a lot of puzzle-solving work in the group and guided everyone to pull together to overcome the difficulties, zhang Xiaoliu in 504, Liao Zhiping in 1401, Liu Yanbo in 1404..

In the face of the new pneumonia epidemic, the temporary party branch played a full role as a fighting fortress, and the majority of Party members, cadres and volunteers played a full role as a pioneer model.

This issue is edited by Chang Chen
